title: Maldives Exports
description: Exports in Maldives decreased to 26.10 USD Million in September from 29.50 USD Million in August of 2022. Exports in Maldives averaged 23.49 USD Million from 2005 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 74.30 USD Million in March of 2008 and a record low of 8 USD Million in July of 2016. The Maldives’ main export product is fish (accounting for over 40 percent of total exports). Others include engines and metal scrap. The Maldives’ main exports partners are France, Thailand, Sri Lanka, Italy, the United Kingdom, Iran, Germany, the Netherlands and the United States. This page provides - Maldives Exports - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Maldives Monetary Authority
